definition.value: The simplest member of the class of 1,4-benzoquinones, obtained by the formal oxidation of hydroquinone to the corresponding diketone. It is a metabolite of benzene.
A hydroxy monocarboxylic acid anion that is the conjugate base of 3-hydroxypropionic acid.
A polyprenyl glycosyl diphosphate having N-acetyl-D-glucosamine as the glycosyl fragment.
A quaternary ammonium ion that is (S)-canadine bearing an N-methyl substituent.
A tripeptide composed of L-tyrosine, L-isoleucine, and L-leucine joined in sequence by peptide linkages.
